data.title: Rosario Ortega - Age, Family, Bio
data.meta_description: Rosario Ortega: her birthday, what she did before fame, her family life, fun trivia facts, popularity rankings, and more.
data.text:
About

Singer whose debut solo album earned her a Grammy Award nomination for Best New Artist in 2012. She has also performed vocal duties for the bands Entre Ríos, The Prostitution and Meteoros.

Before Fame

She lived in Miami, Florida until she was 5 years old, at which point she moved to Tucumán, Argentina. She began studying guitar at age 19, shortly after moving to Buenos Aires.

Trivia

She contributed several songs to the soundtrack for the Ethan Hawke-directed film The Hottest State (2006).

Family Life

She is the daughter of singer Palito Ortega and actress Evangelina Salazar. She is the sister of actress Julieta Ortega, singer Emanuel Ortega and producer Sebastián Ortega.
